        "en": "<p>The Flemish Social Protection (Dutch: ‘Vlaamse Sociale Bescherming’) offers financial assistance to people requiring long-term care.</p><p>The Flemish Social Protection differs from the health insurance, which refunds medical costs and is provided by the health insurance funds. The Flemish Social Protection also has nothing to do with a hospitalization insurance or other additional insurances offered by the health insurance funds.<br>More information is available on the website of the <a href=\"https://www.vlaamsesocialebescherming.be\">Flemish Social Protection</a> (available in Dutch only).</p>",
        "en-x-generated": "<p>Flemish Social Protection (VSB) provides financial assistance to long-term care-dependent people. A first component of Flemish Social Protection is the already existing care budget for severely care-dependent people (formerly called the Flemish care insurance allowance). Since September 2016, the Basic Support Budget or care budget for persons with disabilities has been part of it, and since January 2017 VSB has also been responsible for paying the care budget for elderly people in need of care (formerly called the allowance for assistance to the elderly). Since January 2019, mobility aids have been part of Flemish Social Protection. On top of this, Flemish Social Protection pays for a very large part of the care and staff costs in elderly care (residential care centres, day care centres...).</p><p>Flemish Social Protection is not the same as health insurance and therefore has nothing to do with hospitalisation insurance or other supplementary insurances offered by mutualities.</p>",
